00:00:01.848 --> 00:00:04.040
KATY PRUDIC: Butterflies
are amazing creatures.

00:00:04.040 --> 00:00:07.369
Of course, we admire them for
their beauty and their grace.

00:00:07.369 --> 00:00:09.410
They have many important
roles in an environment.

00:00:09.410 --> 00:00:11.030
They are eating plants.

00:00:11.030 --> 00:00:12.380
They're pollinating plants.

00:00:12.380 --> 00:00:16.040
They're also being eaten
by birds, lizards, mammals.

00:00:16.040 --> 00:00:18.530
Everybody wants to eat
a tasty caterpillar.

00:00:18.530 --> 00:00:22.250
So butterflies are
central to a lot

00:00:22.250 --> 00:00:25.170
of the interactions that are
happening within a community.

00:00:25.170 --> 00:00:26.390
Is that a monarch?

00:00:26.390 --> 00:00:28.475
HANK VERBAIS: Yeah, yeah yeah.

00:00:28.475 --> 00:00:29.720
KATY PRUDIC: And incoming.

00:00:29.720 --> 00:00:31.584
